Package com.orbitz.monitoring.api

Interface Summary
Aggregator Collects monitors
Created May 20, 2010
CompositeMonitor A monitor that holds related submonitors.
Decomposer The contract for classes that takes objects that can not be safely sent across the network and turns them into objects that can be sent.
InheritableStrategy Represents how the MonitoringEngine handles inheritable attributes.
Monitor The contract for all instrumentation objects.
MonitorProcessor An interface for classes that process monitors that are delivered to the monitoring system.
MonitorProcessorAttachable An interface that objects can implement if they support attaching MonitorProcessor instances to themselves.
MonitorProcessorFactory The interface that can be implemented to hook into the process of choosing the processors that are applicable for a given Monitor object.
 

Class Summary
Attribute Standard monitor attribute names
Created May 20, 2010
MonitoringEngine The engine that controls basic correlation of monitors as they are collected and submitted to the engine.
MonitoringLevel MonitoringLevel
 

Exception Summary
AttributeUndefinedException An exception indicating that the requested attribute is undefined.
CantCoerceException An exception used to indicate that the attribute is of the wrong type than should be returned.
